      "docs": "Declares a named invariant for a domain type. Used in DataRole::ValueObject.invariants / Entity.invariants / AggregateRoot.invariants. `name` identifies the invariant (required, must not be empty); `predicate` names the verification mechanism (required). Both fields are required because a nameless invariant is unidentifiable and a predicate-free invariant is unverifiable.",
